-- BMW Group says U.S. sales rise 19.3 pct in August
-- 
-- Tue Sep 4, 2007 3:04pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/09/04/uk-bmw-sales-usa-idUSWEB725520070904

 

 FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - BMW Group ( BMWG.DE ) sales rose 19.3 percent in the United States to 30,639 vehicles in August, the company said in a statement on Tuesday. 

 BMW brand vehicle sales rose 18.5 percent to 26,562 units, while Mini sales rose 25.4 percent to 4,077 cars. This year until the end of August, BMW Group has sold 223,341 vehicles in the United States, 8.1 percent more than in the same period of 2006. (Reporting by  Georgina Prodhan )